Mayael's ability can hinge between "exceptionally good" to "not worth the ![3](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=3&type=symbol)![Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=G&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![White](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=W&type=symbol) mana". Always note that 6 mana is not inexpensive. You also don't activate any "if you cast from the hand" effects. Sorry, [Ulamog](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ulamog) and [Kozilek](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kozilek).   
  
But Naya doesn't truly have any general that really compliments the deck rather than just being the centre of attention. For example, if you made a [Rith, the Awakener](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rith, the Awakener) deck, you'd be very inclined to attack with Rith every turn to make tokens. If you made a [Uril](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Uril) deck, you'd be forced to go full Voltron.  
  
But Mayael doesn't need to be there to make the deck work. You can simply play the whole deck without playing her once. It does defeat the purpose of a Commander deck, but it also means that you won't get handicapped when [Chaos Warp](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chaos Warp) gets played.   
  
That being said, it would've been fantastic if [Hazezon Tamar](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hazezon Tamar) was reprinted and not on the reser... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)
